\begin{frame}{Isobar model and rescattering}
Isobars reflect the fact that the particles in every subchannel interact.
\begin{figure}
 \includegraphics[width=0.8\textwidth]{pictborm/isobar.pdf} 
\end{figure}
But isobar model does not satisfy subchannel unitarity.\\
\vspace{0.2cm}
\begin{block}{Partial waves expansion}
PW = $J^{PC}$ of the system + Isobar + $L$ between the isobar and spectator.
\begin{equation*}
 A = \sum_{\text{partial waves}}
