\begin{frame}{Conclusion}
  \begin{itemize}
  \item Hadron spectroscopy is a reach subject:
    \begin{itemize}
    \item precise data \& sophisticated analysis teach how confined QCD works
    \end{itemize}
  \item The S-matrix principles do not give microscopic picture but gives a way to combine leading effects correctly.
  \item $Z_c(3900)$ is related to several effects: coupled-channels, three-body dynamics.
    \begin{itemize}
    \item We establish the method to find out the leading singularity.
    \item More data are needed to drive the conclusion (especially, $e^+e^-$-energy scan).
    \end{itemize}
  \item $a_1(1420)$ is unique and beautiful phenomenon:% in the light sector
    \begin{itemize}
    \item likely, it is an effect of the rescattering between $3\pi\leftrightarrow K\bar{K}\pi$,
    \item three-body unitarity is required to proceed,
    \item the effect should be seen at $a_1(1260)$ tail from $\tau$-decay.
    \end{itemize}
  \end{itemize}
\end{frame}

