\subsection{Unitarity}
\begin{frame}{Two-body unitarity}{How to take the rescattering into account}
  Conservation of probability gives the unitarity condition
  \begin{equation*}
    SS^\dagger = 1,\quad S = 1+iT \enspace \Rightarrow \enspace T-T^\dagger = i\, T\, T^\dagger
  \end{equation*}
  \begin{equation*}
    \langle f|T|i\rangle = t(s)\,(2\pi)^2\delta(\dots), \quad \Delta_s t = 2i\, t^\star\, \rho\, t.
  \end{equation*}
  The general solution of the unitarity equation is 
  $$
  t(s) = \frac{1}{K^{-1}(s)-ig^2\tilde{\rho}(s)}, \text{ where } \tilde{\rho} = \frac{s}{i \pi}\int \frac{\rho(s')}{s'(s'-s)}\mathrm{d}s'.
  $$\pause
