$$
\text{Disc}_{\sigma'} t_c(\sigma',s,\sigma) = 
\conUpUp{l,\lambda}{l'',\lambda''}\!{\color{red}\Bigg|}\!\disUpUp{l'',\lambda''}{l',\lambda'} +
\conUpDn{l,\lambda}{l'',\lambda''}\!{\color{red}\Bigg|}\!\disUpUp{l'',\lambda''}{l',\lambda'}
$$ 
Using dispersion relations, fix $s,\sigma$,i.e. $A(\sigma') = t_{c}(\sigma',s,\sigma)$:
$$
A(\sigma') = \frac{1}{\pi} \int \frac{\text{Disc}_{\sigma''} t_c(\sigma'',s,\sigma)}{\sigma''-\sigma'} \diff \sigma'' \quad \to \quad\text{Continue in $s$}.
$$
