\begin{frame}{Conclusion}
  \begin{itemize}
  \item Hadron spectroscopy is a rich subject:
    \begin{itemize}
    \item Precise data \& sophisticated analyses teach us how confined QCD works
    \item Naive isobar picture requires rescattering corrections
    \end{itemize}
  \item Three-body unitarity is necessary to understand meson dynamics:
    \vspace{-3mm}
    \begin{itemize}
    \item To establish triangle-singularity effects
    \item To address the question of the presence of poles (molecules, tetraquarks)
    \end{itemize}
  \item $a_1(1420)$ is unique and beautiful phenomenon:
    \begin{itemize}
    \item Small effect, but very solid observation
    \item The presence of the triangle singularity from the coupling $3\pi\leftrightarrow K\bar{K}\pi$ 
      is a model-independent statement
    \end{itemize}
  \end{itemize}
\end{frame}

