\section{Summary}

\begin{frame}{Summary}{Hadron spectroscopy is fascinating}
  \begin{block}{}
    \begin{itemize}
      \item Hadron \textbf{spectroscopy} is a unique tool for understanding the QCD, the theory of matter formation.
      \item \textbf{Diffractive} reaction is a clean setup for measurements of the excitation spectrum
      \item \textbf{COMPASS} leads the effort of large combined light-quark meson studies
    \end{itemize}
  \end{block}
  \begin{alertblock}{The story of $a_1(1420)$}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Peak and phase motion are not unique sign of a resonance!
        \item $a_1(1420)$ signal can be described with ordinary $a_1$ as source
        for the rescattering via the triangle diagram
        \item Old theoretical concept has been clearly observed for the first time!
        \item Intensity of signal $\sim 1\%$, in agreement with experiment
        % \item Formation of complex $K\bar{K}^*$ objects is not excluded,
        % \\ however
        % \item How to find out: $\tau/B$ decays, $K\bar{K}\pi$ final state, etc.
    \end{itemize}
  \end{alertblock}
