\section{Corrections to the Isobar Model}
\subsection{Khuri-Treiman equations}
\begin{frame}{Corrections to the isobar model}
Note, every isobar can rescatter to all others.
\begin{figure}[h!]
 \includegraphics[width=0.25\textwidth]{pict30/rho_s.pdf}\quad {\color{red} $\longrightarrow$}
 \includegraphics[width=0.35\textwidth]{pict30/rho_to_sigma.pdf}\qquad
\end{figure}
\begin{itemize}
 \item First order is determined by the triangle loop diagram. 
 \item Higher order diagram is hard to calculate.
\end{itemize}

%It results to slight redistribution of events on Dalitz plot.
The method to sum whole series of rescattering is known as Khuri-Treiman equations.
It was applied to $\omega,\phi,\eta\to3\pi$, $D\to K^-\pi^+ \pi^+$.
\begin{itemize}
  \item The amplitude of the ``induced'' isobars are given by the loop integral and primary coupling.
  No new parameters appear.
 \end{itemize}
\end{frame}

