\begin{frame}{Conclusions}{}
{\scriptsize
\begin{itemize}
\item The {\bf isobar model} is often a good approximation, while in special cases it may lead to the {\bf incorrect interpretation}.
%but when a narrow resonance sits on the border of the Dalitz plot additional structures
\item The final state interaction in the system of three particles can produce an enhancement in the Dalitz plot.
The effect of the singularity in the triangle diagram appears as a {\bf peak} with a noticeable {\bf phase motion}.
(Possibly, it can explain several XYZ states, pentaquarks candidates).
\item The rescattering processes in coupled channel system cause a migration between the systems {\bf changing the three-body dynamics}.
(likely $a_1(1420)$ is an example)
\item The rescattering series can be taking into account while the two-body interaction is assumed to be known.
\end{itemize}
Ongoing studies:
\begin{itemize}
 \item The general case of the Khuri-Treiman equations (arbitrary quantum numbers), KTA-PWA.
 \item The rescattering equations for coupled channel problem in application to $\pi\pi\pi/\pi KK$ systems.
\end{itemize}
}
\end{frame}

