\item $(\pi\pi)_s$ is a source $\Rightarrow$ $(\pi\pi)_S$ gets modified, $(\pi\pi)_P$ is induced.
  \begin{overpic}[width=0.36\textwidth]{pict/sigmarho.pdf}
    \put(60,10) {\tiny \color{gray}Isobar amplitude}
    \put(60,15) {\tiny Rescatter amplitude}
  \end{overpic}\qquad
  \begin{overpic}[width=0.36\textwidth]{pict/sigmasigma.pdf}
    \put(60,50) {\tiny \color{gray}Isobar amplitude}
    \put(60,45) {\tiny Rescatter amplitude}
  \end{overpic}

\end{itemize}

\end{frame}

\section{Conclusion}
\begin{frame}{Conclusion and outlook}
  Summary
  \begin{itemize}
  \item Isobar model is a rough approximation, unitarity is not satisfied.
  \item Rescattering correction can be significant.
  \item Khuri-Treiman equation gives a tool to deal with a complete series of rescattering.
  \item KT-PWA analysis is promising extension of PWA.    
  \end{itemize}
  \vspace{1cm}
  Prospectives:
  \begin{itemize}
  \item Generalisation of the formalism of the decay of a particle with a spin.
  \item Implementation of formalism for coupled channels.
  \end{itemize}

\end{frame}



