\frame{ \frametitle{SP-corrections to the amplitude}

$K^\star(892) \to K \pi$, $P$-wave decay gives tail to the amplitude.\\
A left-hand singularity is introduce to correct the amplitude 
$g_{K^\star K \pi} \to g_{K^\star K \pi} \times F(k_1)$. $k_1$ is $K^\star$ four-momentum.
{\small
$$
F(k_1) = \frac{M^2 - m_{K^\star}^2}{M^2 - k_1^2}, \quad
M^2 = (m_\pi+m_K)^2 - \frac{4}{R^2}\enspace.
$$
}
$M$ is position of the left singularity, it corresponds to the size of $K^\star$:
{\small $F \approx (1 + R^2 |\vec{p_0} \,|^2)/(1 + R^2 |\vec{p} \,|^2)$}.
$|\vec{p}|$ is $K^\star\to K\pi$ break up momentum.
