\subsection{Interpretation}
\begin{frame}{What is a resonance?}
$$
A = \left[ \enspace
  \begin{tikzpicture}[node distance=0.6cm and 0.9cm,baseline=-0.1cm]
    \coordinate[] (a1); 
    \coordinate[right=of a1] (a2); 
    \coordinate[above right=of a2] (b1); 
    \coordinate[below right=of a2] (b2); 
    \coordinate[above left =of a1] (c1);
    \coordinate[below left =of a1] (c2);

    \draw[vector] (a1) -- node[label=above:{\tiny $a_1(1420)$} ] {} (a2); 
    \draw[scalar] (a2) -- (b1); 
    \draw[scalar] (a2) -- (b2); 
    \draw[scalar] (c1) -- (a1); 
    \draw[scalar] (c2) -- (a1); 
  \end{tikzpicture}
  \enspace \right] \sim
 \frac{1}{m^2-s-i\,m \,\Gamma_{\text{tot}}}
  $$
A resonance is a pole in the amplitude.\\
