To simplify representation, we fix internal masses and \textcolor{cyan}{$\bf s_1$}.\\
Depending on value of $s_1 (y_1)$, we have:
\begin{enumerate}
\item[\tiny $|y_1|<1$] ``No decays'': $M_1<m_1+m_3$, $m_1<M_1+m_3$, $m_3<M_1+m_1$.\\
\begin{itemize}
\item The triangle singularity is known as {\bf anomalous threshold}. It sits below the normal threshold for $s_0$, $s_2$.
\item Appears in form-factors.
\end{itemize} 
\item[\tiny$y_1<-1$] ``Internal decay'': $m_1>M_1+m_3$ or $m_3>M_1+m_1$.\\
\begin{itemize}
\item Position is given by decay kinematics.
\item Appears in decays.
\end{itemize}
\item[\tiny$y_1>1$] ``External decay'': $M_1>m_1+m_3$.\\
{\tiny \textcolor{gray}{Is covered above, just if we choose another variable to fix.}}
\end{enumerate}
