      \begin{block}{The reason of the spurious pole}
        \vspace{-4mm}
        {\scriptsize$$
        \rho(s) \sim \int_{4m_\pi^2}^{(\sqrt{s}-m_\pi)^2}\frac{\diff \sigma}{2\pi} U_\rho(\sigma) \,\frac{\lambda^{1/2}(s,\sigma,m_\pi^2)}{\color{red}s}
        $$}
        \vspace{-4mm}
        \begin{itemize}
          \item Not every pole is the resonance
        \end{itemize}
      \end{block}\pause
      \begin{exampleblock}{Can we find a model without the pole}
        \begin{itemize}
          \item Denoting $\hat t(s) = t(s)/s$
          \vspace{-3mm}
          {\scriptsize$$
            2\text{Im}\, \hat t(s) = \hat t^*(s) \,(s\rho(s))\, \hat t(s),
          $$}\\
          \vspace{-3mm}
          \item New model
          \vspace{-3mm}
          {\scriptsize $$c/(P_k(s) - i g^2 s\hat{\rho}(s)/2)$$
          \\\vspace{-2mm}
          $P_1(s) = m^2-s$\quad does not fit the data\\\pause
          $P_2(s) = s(m^2-s)+h$\quad gives a good fit and the same pole}
      \end{itemize}
      \end{exampleblock}
    \end{column}
  \end{columns}
\end{frame}

\section{Remarks}
\begin{frame}{Summary}
  \begin{exampleblock}{}
    \begin{itemize}
      \item Three-body unitarity is important for hadron spectroscopy
      \begin{itemize}
        \item both experimental and lattice
        \item The light $1^{++}$ sector is the first place to study it
      \end{itemize}
      \item We found a class of models which can satisfy unitarity exactly:
      \begin{itemize}
        \item Factorization and final state interaction.
      \end{itemize}
      \item Free parameters are constrained using ALEPH data\\(where is Belle, BES data !?).
      \item Analytical continuation:
      \begin{itemize}
        \item requires an accurate integral path deformation.
        \item The pole of the $a_1(1260)$ resonance was found.
      \end{itemize}
    \end{itemize}
  \end{exampleblock}%\pause
  \begin{alertblock}{The spurious pole}
    \begin{itemize}
      \item The dynamics in the channel requires strong influence of the left singularities
      (the threshold region is important).
      % \item  is important for the value of the width.
      \item Systematic studies are ongoing.
      % \item We have not found the parametrization
    \end{itemize}
  \end{alertblock}
\end{frame}

