\begin{frame}{Summary}
    \begin{block}{}
        $1P$ mupltiplet of ``bad'' diquark -- a fundamental piece of the baryon spectroscopy puzzle
        \begin{itemize}
            \item 7 states: five $\lambda$-modes and two $\rho$-modes
            \item In common for $\Xi$, $\Sigma_{b/c}$, $\Omega_{b/c}$, $\Xi_{b/c}$, $\Xi_{cc}$
            \item State splittings indicate spin-orbit and ``hyperfine'' interaction
            \item Charm (beaty) baryons are narrow -- good chance to resolve it:
            \begin{itemize}
                \item Assign quantum numbers, reveal the light quark dynamics
                \item Identify diquark excitation for the first time
            \end{itemize}
        \end{itemize}
    \end{block}
    \vspace{5mm}
    \begin{columns}
        \begin{column}[]{0.45\textwidth}
            \begin{exampleblock}{\centering The threshold structure}
            \begin{itemize}
                \item Is a state?\\Compact / Molecular component?
                \item Present at other sectors?
            \end{itemize}
            \end{exampleblock}
        \end{column}
        \begin{column}[]{0.45\textwidth}
            \begin{exampleblock}{\centering The fifth narrow state}
            \begin{itemize}
                \item Why only seen in inclusive $\Xi_c^+ K^-$
                \item The first manifestation of the diquark excitation?
                $2S$ states?
            \end{itemize}
        \end{exampleblock}
    \end{column}
    \end{columns}
\end{frame}

