\begin{frame}{Summary}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textbf{Unitarity} is an important constraint
        \begin{itemize}
            \item that guides the amplitude construction\\
            \paper{Mai et al.(EPJ A53 (2017)), Jackura et al.(EPJ C79 (2019)), MM et al. (JPAC) 1904.11894}
            \item is satisfied in a good FT consideration \paper{R.Briceno, 1905.11188}
        \end{itemize}
        % \item Unitarity still leaves a lot of freedom:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Separation between the short-range and the long-range is not unique \paper{M.Doering et al., PLB681 (2009) 26-31}
            \item Decomposition of the short-range is not unique \paper{A.Jackura et al., 1905.12007}
        \end{itemize}
        \vspace{5mm}
        \item The \textbf{ladder} is a new phenomenon of the three-particle physics
        \begin{itemize}
            \item sum of particle exchange diagrams
            \item left-hand singularity in the physical region
            \item genuine non-factorizable component
        \end{itemize}
        \item The \textbf{resonance} part admits Factorization:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Effect of the \textbf{Ladder} is the common final-state interaction
            \item Unitarity requirement casts to the familiar two-body-like form.
        \end{itemize}
    \end{itemize}\pause
    \vspace{-3cm}
    \begin{exampleblock}{Outlook}
        Better understanding of the exchange processes is needed:\\
        \begin{enumerate}
            \item[$\Rightarrow$] studies of the final-state interaction in the decays
            \item[$\Rightarrow$] studies of the fix-target production data (COMPASS, GlueX)
            \vspace{3mm}
            \item[$\Rightarrow$] \textbf{studies of the nice, clean scattering data from the lattice}
        \end{enumerate}
    \end{exampleblock}
\end{frame}

