      \begin{enumerate}
        \item Formulate amplitude model \textbf{symbolically} \\ with a Computer Algebra System
        \item Use that symbolic expression as \textbf{template to a computational back-end}, such as a differentiable programming framework
      \end{enumerate}
      We selected \textbf{\color{red}JAX} as the fastest back-end
    \end{minipage}
  }\only<2>{%
    \begin{minipage}[t][0.85\textheight][t]{0.64\textwidth}
      \raggedright
      Advantages of this workflow:
      \setlength{\leftmargini}{1.5em}
      \begin{itemize}
        \item Computational implementation is \textbf{outsourced to fast, optimized back-ends} from the Machine Learning and data science community
        \item Out-of-the-box GPU and multi-threading support
        \item Very easy to implement other parametrizations without having to worry about performance
        \item CAS simplifications result in performance boosts
        \item Symbolic amplitude models result in a \textbf{self-documenting workflow}
      \end{itemize}~\\[-0.5em]
      Works especially well for large computational models
    \end{minipage}
