\begin{frame}{Local conclusion-I}
\begin{itemize}
\item Schmid cancelation is valid only for an elastic case.
\item In presence of inelastisity the effect of a triangle diagram appears {\bf in projections} for fixed total inveriant mass and {\bf in 3-particle mass distribution} for fixed final state.
\item The analytical relations for amplitude in the limit of triangle singularity can be written.
\item $Z(3900)$ at $J/\Psi\,\pi$ is very good candidate to test the approach:
\begin{itemize}
\item The peak is observed in several reactions ($\Psi'(4160)\to J/\Psi\pi\pi$ and $Y(4260)\to J/\Psi\pi\pi$),
\item $Y(4260)\to D^\star D \pi$ data are available.
\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}

