The problem with parameters of $f_0$ is scaling behaviour near $K\bar{K}$ threshold. It results in $R = g_{KK}^2/g_{\pi\pi}^2$ is known (more or less) $\approx 3\dots 4$, branching ratio $f_0\to\pi\pi$ is $\approx 0.4$, but $g_{KK}$, $g_{\pi\pi}$ variates.
$$
\bar{g}_{\pi\pi} = \frac{g_{\pi\pi}^2}{8\pi m_{f_0}^2} = \textcolor{blue}{0.1} \dots \textcolor{orange}{0.6}
$$
