\begin{frame}{Summary}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Amplitude $X\to V (\mu\mu) V(\mu\mu)$ depends on 3 angles (5 angles) for the unpolarized (polarized) production.
  \item Decay of $X\to VV$ is fully determined by $3\times 3$ matrix of the helicity couplings
  \item Parity + permutation symmetry constraint the matrix {\color{gray} (+ particle-2 phase)}
  \begin{align*}
    H_{\lambda_1,\lambda_2} &= (-1)^{J} \,\eta_{X} \,H_{-\lambda_1,-\lambda_2}, &
    H_{\lambda_1,\lambda_2} &= (-1)^{J} H_{\lambda_2,\lambda_1}.
  \end{align*}
  \item There are four groups of quantum numbers, $J^{P}$: odd vs even, natural vs unnatural
  \item Likelihood test is the most powerful method
  \item $\phi$-dependence is single-variable discriminating observable
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}



