\begin{frame}{Strong transitions to a baryon and a pseudoscalar}{}
    \vspace{-5mm}
    \begin{align*}
        \Omega_c^{**0} &\to \Xi_c^+K^- & \Xi_c^{**0} &\to \Lambda_c^+K^- & \color{gray}\Sigma_c^{**0} & \color{gray}\to \Lambda_c^+\pi^-\\
        \Omega_b^{**-} &\to \Xi_b^0K^- & \Xi_b^{**-} &\to \Lambda_b^0K^- & \color{gray}\Sigma_b^{**-} & \color{gray}\to \Lambda_b^0\pi^-
    \end{align*}
    HQSS ($m_Q\to \infty$) gives the selection rule based on the light d.o.f.~\paper{Chiladze, Falk, PRD 56 (1997)}\\
    Can be applied to the decay to ground-state baryon and pseudoscalar ($B+P$):
