\begin{frame}{Minimizers}{Replace \texttt{Minuit}}
  Optimizers in Julia:
  \begin{itemize}
    \item \texttt{Optim.jl}: implement \texttt{BFGS}
    \begin{itemize}
      \item Suggests a common interface of minimization: \texttt{NLSolversBase}
    \end{itemize}
    \item \texttt{NLopt.jl}: calls \texttt{BFGS}
    \begin{itemize}
      \item C++ wrapper, works
    \end{itemize}
    \item \texttt{iminuit} via \texttt{PyCall.jl}: calls \texttt{MIGRAD}, pre-version of \texttt{BFGS}
    \begin{itemize}
      \item Incredibly stable linear search, works where other (above) fail
      \item \texttt{iminuit} $1.54 \to 2.7.0$: versioning via \texttt{Conda.jl} is not straightforward
    \end{itemize}
  \end{itemize}
\end{frame}

