\section{Summary}

\begin{frame}{Summary}

  \begin{exampleblock}{}
    \begin{itemize}
      \item \textbf{Hadron spectroscopy is an unique environment to understand
      an interplay between the QM d.o.f. and nuclei d.o.f.}
      \item Might be a key to the progress in understating of QCD in confined regime
    \end{itemize}  
  \end{exampleblock}\vspace{4mm}\pause
  \begin{block}{Scattering parameters and compositeness}
    \begin{itemize}
      \item $a$, $r$ are fundamental parameters of hadronic interactions that can be measured.
      \item Weinberg compositeness is an attractive concept that gives an intuitive interpretation, however
      \item Misses rigorous validation e.g.\ using lattice QCD
    \end{itemize}
  \end{block}
  Many new exotic states observed at LHCb, and other experiments:
  \begin{itemize}
    \item Some might turn out to be purely nuclei (hadronic molecules),
    \item Some clearly involve quark dynamics
  \end{itemize}
\end{frame}

