\begin{frame}{Upper limit of the effective range~\paper{MM, 2203.04622}}
  {\small
  $$
  -16.2(-21.2) < \text{Re}\,r < -4.3\text{ at } 90(95)\%\text{ CL}\,.
  $$}
  The effective range has a \textbf{\color{colb}hard limit} from above in the model,
  The \textbf{\color{colb} low limit} is constrained by fit to the data.\\[3mm]
  In the contact-interaction limit ($g\to \infty$), the model is parameterless.
  The upper limit can be broken down into components:
  $$r = r_\text{qtb} + \Delta r_\text{ope} + \Delta r_\text{high}$$\,. % 4.36
  \begin{align*}
    r_\text{qtb} &= 0.16\,\text{fm}\,\quad \text{two-body look function},\\ % -0.02i
    \Delta r_\text{ope} &= -0.94\,\text{fm}\quad \text{effect of real pion exchange}\,,\\% -0.28 i
    \Delta r_\text{high} &= -3.7\,\text{fm}\quad \text{effect of }D^{*0}D^+\,, % +0.3i
  \end{align*}
\end{frame}


